{
  "texts": [
    "The main performance metric is the execution time.",
    "Since vPIM is the first system to enable virtualization for processingin-memory devices, we use native execution time as the baseline and evaluate the virtualization overhead introduced by vPIM.",
    "We also use two sets of breakdowns.",
    "The first is application-centric, breaking the total execution time into data transfer (CPU-DPU, DPU-CPU, Inter-DPU) and program execution (DPU).",
    "The second is driver-centric, where we draw insights into how the workflow for different rank operations contributes to the total execution time."
  ]
}